      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:46:13",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ (صلى الله عليه وآله) عَلَيْكُمْ بِالسَّفَرِ بِاللَّيْلِ فَإِنَّ الْأَرْضَ تُطْوَى بِاللَّيْلِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473620\">H 14937</a> – Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al-Nowfaly, from Al-Sakuny, who has narrated the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The Rasool Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘It is on you to travel at night, for the ground folds up at night’. "
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "490. A number of our companions, Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Ismail Bin Mahraan, from Sayf Bin Umeyra, from Basheer Al-Nabaal, from Humraan Bin Ayn who said: I said to Abu Ja’far (a.s.), ‘The people are saying the earth would fold up for us at night, how it would fold up?’ He (a.s.) said: ‘Like this’, then folded his (a.s.) cloth’."
        ]
      }
    },
